This POC uses a standard autotools configure-mechanism. For an introduction
to the autotools, see for example

http://sources.redhat.com/autobook/autobook/autobook_toc.html

INITIAL STEP
============

"./autogen.sh" must be called at first to generate the configure script.
This requires the autotools (autoconf/automake/libtool).


CONFIGURE
=========

Examples:

a) Own boost installation

./configure --with-boost-flavor=gcc41-mt-1_36 \
	--with-boost=$HOME/boost/include/boost-1_36 \
	LDFLAGS=-L$HOME/boost/lib

or

./configure EXTRA_PREFIXES=$HOME/boost

For more options see the output of "./configure --help".

RUN
====

  python example.py <random parameters>

or

  mpi/espresso_embedded example.py <random parameters>

Problems
========

- currently, installing does not work

- in case you have several versions of boost installed, it is recommended to specify the
  boost include directory and boost flavor manually to make sure the correct version is
  used